cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.NE 

The paper discusses a neural network system for autonomous driving that is trained using road images and steering angles generated by a human driver. The focus is on explaining how the system makes its decisions, which suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The system is based on deep learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The system is designed for autonomous driving, which falls under robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the system is based on a neural network, which is a common tool in the field of neural networks (cs.NE).
